{"title":"“NokiApple LumiPhone 1020 SE” merges Windows Phone body with budget iPhone guts","link":"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2025/02/windows-lumiphone-modder-elegantly-fits-2022-iphone-into-2013-nokia-body/","date":1739822430000,"content":"<p>Remember the Lumia 1020? It's back—in iPhone SE form.</p>\n<p>The Lumia 1020 was a lot of smartphone in July 2013. It debuted with a focus \"almost entirely on the phone's massive camera,\" <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2013/07/in-the-dark-and-on-the-move-with-the-nokia-lumia-1020s-camera/\">Ars wrote at the time</a>. That big 41-megapixel sensor jutted forth from the phone body, and Nokia reps showed off its low-light, rapid-motion camera abilities by shooting pictures of breakdancers in a dark demonstration room. The company also offered an optional camera grip—one that made it feel a lot more like a point-and-shoot camera. In a more robust review, Ars suggested <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2013/08/the-nokia-lumia-1020-the-smartphone-to-render-point-and-shoots-obsolete/\">the Lumia 1020 might actually make the point-and-shoot obsolete</a>.</p>\n<figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"700\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-lumia1020-holding-2048x1400-1-1024x700.jpeg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-lumia1020-holding-2048x1400-1-1024x700.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-lumia1020-holding-2048x1400-1-640x438.jpeg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-lumia1020-holding-2048x1400-1-768x525.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-lumia1020-holding-2048x1400-1-1536x1050.jpeg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-lumia1020-holding-2048x1400-1-980x670.jpeg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-lumia1020-holding-2048x1400-1-1440x984.jpeg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-lumia1020-holding-2048x1400-1.jpeg 2048w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      Front of the Lumia 1020, showing a bit of Windows Phone square grid flair.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Casey Johnston\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"1579\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lumia_back-1024x1579.jpeg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lumia_back-1024x1579.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lumia_back-640x987.jpeg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lumia_back-768x1184.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lumia_back-996x1536.jpeg 996w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lumia_back-1328x2048.jpeg 1328w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lumia_back-980x1511.jpeg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lumia_back-1440x2220.jpeg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lumia_back.jpeg 1562w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      Back of the Lumia 1020, with oh-so-much yellow.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Casey Johnston\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n      <figure>\n      <img width=\"1024\" height=\"727\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-camera-grip-2048x1454-1-1024x727.jpeg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-camera-grip-2048x1454-1-1024x727.jpeg 1024w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-camera-grip-2048x1454-1-640x454.jpeg 640w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-camera-grip-2048x1454-1-768x545.jpeg 768w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-camera-grip-2048x1454-1-1536x1091.jpeg 1536w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-camera-grip-2048x1454-1-980x696.jpeg 980w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-camera-grip-2048x1454-1-1440x1022.jpeg 1440w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/nokia-camera-grip-2048x1454-1.jpeg 2048w\" />\n      <figcaption>\n        <div>\n    <div></div>\n    <div>\n      The accessory camera grip for the Lumia 1020, shown at its press reveal.\n\n              <span>\n          Credit:\n\n          \n          Casey Johnston\n\n                  </span>\n          </div>\n  </div>\n      </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n  \n<p>The Lumia 1020 contained yet another cutting edge concept of the day: Windows Phone, Microsoft's color-coded, square-shaped companion to its mobile-forward Windows 8. The mobile OS never got over the users/apps, chicken/egg conundrum, and <a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2017/10/windows-phone-is-now-officially-dead-a-sad-tale-of-what-might-have-been/\">called it quits in October 2017</a>. The end of that distant-third-place mobile OS would normally signal the end of the Lumia 1020 as a usable phone.</p><p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2025/02/windows-lumiphone-modder-elegantly-fits-2022-iphone-into-2013-nokia-body/\">Read full article</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2025/02/windows-lumiphone-modder-elegantly-fits-2022-iphone-into-2013-nokia-body/#comments\">Comments</a></p>","author":"Kevin Purdy","siteTitle":"Ars Technica","siteHash":"5b0ddf6e8923e49262a7894cfd77962733e43fbcc565a103b48373820b310636","entryHash":"5a99f97f04062c0a410084dcfe99998c1b72e74935e1b2a3666806d112cbd2cc","category":"Tech"}